title: a1502 missing L7430 (PPDDR_S3_REG_R)
message: hello i got a a1502 that was touched by  another shop. it shows green light on the magsafe but it doesn't turn on. After visual inspection, i saw that it was missing a inductor L7430 on the line ppddr_s3_reg_r. could this missing component cause a bigger problem (i.e frying cpu)? i tried to find a donor but i wasnt able to find one with similar specs.

title: a1502 missing L7430 (PPDDR_S3_REG_R)
message: It should show an orange light. L7430 was removed for a reason I guess. First thing to check would be a short to GND on either side.

title: a1502 missing L7430 (PPDDR_S3_REG_R)
message: Sorry I meant orange light. No short on either side. My diode mode reading on both pads is about 0.128

title: a1502 missing L7430 (PPDDR_S3_REG_R)
message: Should not have caused damage, put one back and go from there.

title: a1502 missing L7430 (PPDDR_S3_REG_R)
message: got the fan spinning and chime after replacing l7430 and isl6259. Now i need to figure the image problem. im waiting for a new lcd

title: a1502 missing L7430 (PPDDR_S3_REG_R)
message: 820-3476 is the 2014 model not the 2015 model. And yes you can replace just the LCD cable very easily on Retinas just have to remove spine.
